    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Retailer Perception on Soft Drinks with Special Reference to Hindustan Coca-Cola Beverages Pvt.Ltd</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">V. Sivasomasekhar</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Soft Drinks<br />Hindustan Coca-Cola</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P4722</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Soft drinks are a non-alcoholic drink which is to be consumed chilled, and does not stimulate one’s nervous system. The ingredients of the soft drinks are flavor, water and carbon-di-oxide gas. The buyers are of all age groups and both sex.
Soft drink has been manufactured since long time. They are of various flavors like Orange, Lemon, Mango, and Cola. In India, aerated waters also known as ‘soda’ was first introduced since time immemorial, which is still popular with the masses due to its low price.
Aerated waters soft drinks may be divided into two classes namely Aerated Table Waters and effervescent beverages. The effervescent beverages are flavored and are known as ‘Soda Water’, ‘Soda’ and these include ginger ales. Natural and Synthetic flavors are used and synthetic flavors are the outcome of laboratory experiments.
Artificially aerated waters had their inception in Priestley’s success in 1972 in producing aerated mineral spring water. Large scale manufacture of aerated waters was started by “Paul” at Geneva and afterwards by “Schweppes” in London. In United States of America a person added fruit juice as flavor and soft drink industry started from then onwards.
From the original conception of the imitation of the natural carbonated waters from springs the industry has broadened to include the production of aerated sweetened drinks and substitutes for beverage such as cider which are aerated by fermentation. The technique of large aerated water manufacture and the operators have undergone considerable improvement.
Scientific and technological progress has changed the phase of every-day life of man and soft drink industry is not an exception. The latest science and technology has improved the quality as well as the quantity of the production. The incredible progress achieved in transportation distributes the drinks to every nook and corner of the country. In view of the rapid progress and spread of the soft drink’s production, if the industry caters to the tastes and needs of its consumers the industry attains large dimensions.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8289">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8289</a></td></tr>
